{"type":"message","id":"467ea9ae","parentId":"e27aede1","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:33:35.440Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ub5sc23mvyrp_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 083220\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: scripts/tic-classifier.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. I have established a sandbox foundation and completed architecture cross-analysis\r\n2. I've discovered the compression-causal duality - that compression and causal discovery are the same problem\r\n3. The next action is to implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on pulse logs\r\n4. I need to measure invariant/variant classification accuracy and predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions:\r\n- Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n- Define significance scoring\r\n- Tune λ empirically\r\n- Wire to TemporalAttention backend\r\n- Measure compression ratio\r\n- Implement TIC classifier (NEW - from Phase 1 Advancement)\r\n\r\nThe most critical next action is the TIC experiment as it advances Phase 1 and potentially Phase 2 (collapsing them into one unified problem).\r\n\r\nLet me implement a TIC classifier that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Classifies content as invariant (persisting across pulses) vs variant (changing)\r\n3. Attempts to predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nI'll create a PowerShell script for this experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight reveals that the TIC experiment is the critical next step to validate the unified Phase 1/2 hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns in pulse logs and tests prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `experiments/tic_classifier.ps1` - a PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Loads last 20 pulse logs\r\n2. Extracts recurring patterns (invariants) vs transient changes (variants)\r\n3. Attempts to predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n4. Reports classification accuracy and prediction precision\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC: Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\n# Tests hypothesis: Causal structure = Invariant structure\r\n# Success: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$PulseCount = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\",\r\n    [double]$InvarianceThreshold = 0.7\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# Load pulse logs\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Experiment ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Loading last $PulseCount pulse logs...\"\r\n\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem \"$LogDir/pulse_*.md\" | \r\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \r\n    Select-Object -First $PulseCount\r\n\r\nif ($pulseFiles.Count -lt 3) {\r\n    Write-Host \"Insufficient pulse logs for experiment\" -ForegroundColor Red\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Found $($pulseFiles.Count) pulse logs\"\r\n\r\n# Parse pulse content\r\n$pulses = @()\r\nforeach ($file in $pulseFiles) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $file.FullName -Raw\r\n    $pulses += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        File = $file.Name\r\n        Content = $content\r\n        Timestamp = $file.LastWriteTime\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Extract key-value pairs and structural patterns from each pulse\r\nfunction Extract-Patterns {\r\n    param([string]$content)\r\n    \r\n    $patterns = @{\r\n        Goals = @()\r\n        Insights = @()\r\n        Actions = @()\r\n        Files = @()\r\n        Metrics = @()\r\n        Raw = $content\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract ## headers (section structure)\r\n    $headers = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?m)^##\\s+(.+)$')\r\n    foreach ($h in $headers) {\r\n        $patterns.Goals += $h.Groups[1].Value.Trim()\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract - [ ] todo items\r\n    $todos = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?m)^-\\s+\\[ \\]\\s+(.+)$')\r\n    foreach ($t in $todos) {\r\n        $patterns.Actions += $t.Groups[1].Value.Trim()\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract file references\r\n    $files = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?m)(?:file:|`)([a-zA-Z0-9_/.-]+\\.[a-z]{2,4})`')\r\n    foreach ($f in $files) {\r\n        $patterns.Files += $f.Groups[1].Value\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract key metrics (pattern: word: value)\r\n    $metrics = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?m)^([^:\\n]+):\\s*([\\d.]+|[\\d.]+%|true|false)')\r\n    foreach ($m in $metrics) {\r\n        $patterns.Metrics += \"$($m.Groups[1].Value): $($m.Groups[2].Value)\"\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return $patterns\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Extract patterns from all pulses\r\nWrite-Host \"Extracting patterns...\"\r\n$extracted = @()\r\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $pulses.Count; $i++) {\r\n    $patterns = Extract-Patterns $pulses[$i].Content\r\n    $extracted += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        Index = $i\r\n        File = $pulses[$i].File\r\n        Patterns = $patterns\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Identify INVARIANTS (patterns appearing in multiple pulses)\r\nWrite-Host \"Identifying invariants...\"\r\n$allGoals = @{}\r\n$allActions = @{}\r\n$allFiles = @{}\r\n$allMetrics = @{}\r\n\r\nforeach ($e in $extracted) {\r\n    foreach ($g in $e.Patterns.Goals) {\r\n        if ($allGoals.ContainsKey($g)) { $allGoals[$g]++ } else { $allGoals[$g] = 1 }\r\n    }\r\n    foreach ($a in $e.Patterns.Actions) {\r\n        if ($allActions.ContainsKey($a)) { $allActions[$\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 08:32:50\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774355615435}}
